    {
      "type": "comment",
      "content": " A tiny time budget (20ms) wrapping a sleep that overruns it. The"
    },
    {
      "type": "comment",
      "content": " timer fires while the JS-bodied sleep is in flight; sleep is"
    },
    {
      "type": "comment",
      "content": " abortable, so it wakes promptly on the guard's abort signal. The"
    },
    {
      "type": "comment",
      "content": " next runner step boundary then throws GuardExceededError(\"time\","
    },
    {
      "type": "comment",
      "content": " ...). The stdlib guard's `try` converts it to a Failure with type"
    },
    {
      "type": "comment",
      "content": " \"timeoutFailure\". We assert actualTime is a real elapsed"
    },
    {
      "type": "comment",
      "content": " measurement (at least half the budget) rather than a 0/sentinel"
    },
    {
      "type": "comment",
      "content": " value; see the comment on the assertion below for why the bound is"
    },
    {
      "type": "comment",
      "content": " deliberately loose."
    },
    {
      "type": "comment",
      "content": " The handler is race insurance, not part of the pinned behavior: on a"
    },
    {
      "type": "comment",
      "content": " slow runner the walk from pushGuard to the sleep can eat the whole"
    },
    {
      "type": "comment",
      "content": " 20ms budget, so the trip is DETECTED at a step boundary and raised"
    },
    {
      "type": "comment",
      "content": " as a resumable interrupt instead of aborting the in-flight sleep."
    },
    {
      "type": "comment",
      "content": " Rejecting it delivers the same GuardExceededError from the step, and"
    },
    {
      "type": "comment",
      "content": " the output is identical on both paths. On a fast run the handler"
    },
    {
      "type": "comment",
      "content": " never fires."
    },
