              "thenBody": [
                {
                  "type": "comment",
                  "content": " actualTime is measured with performance.now(), while the guard's"
                },
                {
                  "type": "comment",
                  "content": " timer fires off libuv's coarser millisecond clock, and loaded CI"
                },
                {
                  "type": "comment",
                  "content": " runners add scheduling latency on top — the two readings can"
                },
                {
                  "type": "comment",
                  "content": " disagree by MORE than the 2ms this test used to allow (issue"
                },
                {
                  "type": "comment",
                  "content": " #467: it flaked at exactly that boundary). The property worth"
                },
                {
                  "type": "comment",
                  "content": " asserting is that actualTime is a real measurement rather than a"
                },
                {
                  "type": "comment",
                  "content": " 0/sentinel value, so require it to reach half the budget: immune"
                },
                {
                  "type": "comment",
                  "content": " to any plausible clock skew, still catches a broken measurement."
